description.narrative: UNICEF supported capacity development for social service workforce and other child protection (CP) stakeholders in different sectors including justice, education and health, leading to provision of improved case management services to more than 14,000 at-risk children, victims of violence and children in contact with the law; in-person psychosocial support for more than 25,000 children and over 8,000 children through COVID-19 response. Over 1.7;million people were engaged through community mobilization platforms including knocking door campaigns to promote Female Genital Mutilation (FGM) elimination. UNICEF’s advocacy led to application of non-custodial alternative measures and restorative justice for children in contact with the law. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:02/01/2022
